ty and people aren't interested.  I do have some good items, but I had to buy them with my hard earned (and sometimes farmed) money, the only remaining items I quested for being crafted.  There are tons of good stuff to be had, but getting it doesn't seem very plausible.  <br><br>Example, im 45, and I wear a rockhopper hide belt of 6 ac.  There are plenty good belts out there, but getting them means going in a zone to find it empty or to try and find a party willing to do the 6 hour camp for it which most wont.<br><br>Hmmm, what are your solutions to this?  Although I check those who sell in the forum, but most are the same people who can either farm/camp easily or just solo everything.<br><br>[/Tv is starting to show stuff]<br><br>(Don't I always have the most negative posts... and yeah, the server is STILL dying) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 7:23:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone else notice how hard it is to quest or find gear.</span><hr size=1> *smile*<br>I've had no problems getting quests done on FV, or going with a group to do item camps either for that matter. I even had folks help me camp Grimblox in Sol A, for 3 days in about 12 hour sessions. All for an item that I prolly won't have a chance at for months.<br>*grin*<br>and I'm lower level than you. So it's all about guild and friends.<br><br>But I've said that before. <br><br>There are 2 big problems with the  Luclin quest armors is the lack of resist. Sure you can fight mobs that aren't casters but I'd rather fight the fun stuff that casts and have armor with good resists on it, to cut down the AE damage for me. Also folks with &quot;ok&quot; systems are in a world of hurt on Luclin because of the new graphips oh and the umbra /amd issue.<br><br>so to answer your question : No I haven't had a problem with folks not lending me a helping hand on quest items. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bren>bren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 7:25:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone else notice how hard it is to quest or find gear.</span><hr size=1> Geeze all those posts of new people joining the server had me misled.<br><br>Join Ephriam, Finneas, Alora and myself late nights.  All we have been doing lately is hunting places to help folks get relevant gear and quest items (and loot).  A few more seasons under our belts and we'll be stalking the RyGorr.<br><br>Brendel<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulexxiclockwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lexxi Clockwork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 7:26:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Easy to find quest gear and the server is doing GREAT!</span><hr size=1>      Hmmm, I cannot solo and at level 25 I have 50 points of wisdom gear. I do have lots of friends and we take turn going for quest items. My suggestion is join a guild and fill up your friends list.<br><br>&lt;SMILE&gt;<br><br>Lexxi Ledenyetz<br>25th Prayer<br>Cleric of Brell<br>Ak'Anon<br>CSO and Heiress - Ledenyetz Troupe<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 7:42:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well ..</span><hr size=1> .. that's not really any different than any other server.  Everyone has something they want.  Deciding on which want to satisfy with the group's time is hard to do.  The nicer part of being in a guild is that guildies tend to have a longer memory for favors when you helped them out getting gear.<br><br>Even then, if the camp is unpleasant, it can be hard to get help.  For instance, on old server with my old monk, it was cake to get help for Chardok pipe -- great xp, empty zone.  Getting help for Karnor's pipe was like pulling teeth.  XP isn't too hot and the zone is just packed with r00d d00ds arguing over every spawn in sight.  I detested KC myself, so I really understood why folks didn't flock to help every single day.  The only spot in KC we liked for xp was the sewers -- the d00ds died trying to get in, so we had it to ourselves mostly.<br><br>Anyway, I feel for you -- been there before.  I wouldn't worry so much about gear, though.  Get in enough xp groups in various spots and gear will happen mostly by itself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxreynnx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>x Reynn x</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 8:03:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well ..</span><hr size=1> Why not type /who friends all.  That should solve your problem of not getting help with gear and quest items. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 282<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 8:38:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well ..</span><hr size=1> Bjond, <br>I still have your polished steel Ulak, its cluttering my bank with more stuff that people never picked up even though I was giving it away.<br><br><br>As for quests, I have pieces to do crafted, lambent, Ro and other stuff like mage research, mage epic, but those are all pointless quests that to me are worth nothing, its the same quests people do.<br><br>Right now I'm trying to get Jboots and I do have a cleric by my side but other than that, most people settle for low risk, high experience reward instead of high risk, high treasure, low experience. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uitchibumbashalots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ItchibumBashalots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 258<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 8:49:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone else notice how hard it is to quest or find gear.</span><hr size=1> Depends on how you look at it.<br><br>I have died a few times as of late taking risks.  We have dont some gnarly quests.  We have taken some big risks....but easy to do when you can FD eheh....unless its with a bunch of caster but heads blasting you away....ie the noble room in guk....ate me alive a level or two ago...sucked.<br><br>BTW Bjond....ill post on Fen's selling post when I get another PSU so keep checkin for it there LOL.<br><br>Making friends is key.  Scratchy and I are 45ish and ready to start banging some cool zones out to break the hell level and hit 50.  But in doing that we want to make sure we have done EVERYTHING else too.  I want to see it all before I hang it up after Ichi.  Im trying to make as many friends as possible....think I can write Haegen out, not sure what he has against me but oh well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ....and get them together for fun.<br><br>Make friends!<br><br>Ichi<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 329<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 9:28:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks for holding it Fen!</span><hr size=1> I have you on friends and look for you every time I'm online.  I think we must play on opposite sides of the world or at least on opposite polarity schedules.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 486<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/30/02 1:43:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: items</span><hr size=1> Get... some... friends!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Really, get some.  Then figure out some zones that you can hunt in that provide items for all of you, or work out a rotating quest system (ie: help me get such n such today, and I'll help you get such n such tomorrow).<br><br>Or if that's too much work, just do some good XP camp that offers treasure ya don't need (like guise of deception), and offer it as a reward to lower level characters if they get the quest stuff for ya.  <br><br>I've found that the removal of no_drop restrictions, combined with the 1 character per account limitation, has created this massive overstock of armor and equipment.  Most of the higher level characters have bank boxes full of good stuff that they're willing to trade if you spend the time completing lower level quests that just take a while (like coldain rings, staff of temperate flux, ulthork tusks, etc).<br><br>- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyrdup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 5:00:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well</span><hr size=1> I'd say your problems is friends.  i remember thinking of you as a friend loooong ago... and not being treated like one, so I took you off my list.<br><br>/shrug<br><br>I dont have problems getting gear <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p><center><i><a href=mailto:kyrial_moonlight@lycos.com>Kyrial Moonlight</a><BR><font color=white>A light shines upon us all.</font></I><P>Wyrd Windwalker.  Kyrial Darkflame.</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxenojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XENOJONES</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/1/02 9:00:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> I spent alot of time in Luclin trying to accumulate items for the new armor quests and all I got were copious amounts of trash IMHO. I must have had 40 different twilight quest items few which matched with the oth