 is smaller than normal.<br><br>Lambent Armor is widely considered pretty good midlevel Bard armor.  People know its stats, what it looks like, and are reasonably familiar with the zones you need to traverse.  Nobody know what the Twilight Bard armor is, what stats it has, what it looks like, or even how to get there.  So is it any surprise that people seek out Lambent?<br><br>I imagine that after the Twilight Armor is fully documented, you will see an upsurge in the popularity.  But most people with limited resources and limited play time are going to pick the Good Prizes over taking the Mystery Item behind Curtain Number One.<br><br>You sound like you might be one of those Intrepid Explorers Feneant, and if so, that's cool.  What you need to do is find other Intrepid Explorers, and work together to find these new things, explore the new Luclin Zones.<br><br>I don't think you're going to have great luck with pickup groups in that regard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1226.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1226.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1226.topic&index=12><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.threadControl?topicID=1226.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1226.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of re